New German warship once again delayed
The latest German navy fragate should have entered the service in 2014 to replace warships of the Cold War time, however, it will be necessary to wait at least until next year due to systems likely to fault and an exponential growth cost, according to local media.
The entry to the service of the "Rheinland-Pfalz," the commanding ship of the Baden-Württemberg class's eighty fregates, has now been postponed until the first half of 2019, according to the newspaper Die Zeit quoting a military spokesman.
